Ref URL:
https://www.nginx.com/resources/admin-guide/restricting-access-auth-basic/


sudo apt-get install apache2-utils

sudo htpasswd -c /etc/apache2/.htpasswd user1

adding first user:
sudo htpasswd -c /etc/apache2/.htpasswd gooru
password:netops@gooru40

adding second user:
sudo htpasswd /etc/apache2/.htpasswd pune_team
passwd:pune_team@goorU


netops@gooru40

in the config file, edit below entries:


      location / {
           auth_basic “Administrator’s Area”;
           auth_basic_user_file /etc/apache2/.htpasswd;
      }

